        ": سَأَلَهُ أَبِي وَ أَنَا أَسْمَعُ عَنْ حَدِّ اَلْمَرَضِ اَلَّذِي يَتْرُكُ اَلْإِنْسَانُ فِيهِ اَلصَّوْمَ قَالَ «إِذَا لَمْ يَسْتَطِعْ أَنْ يَتَسَحَّرَ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1943 - Bakr ibn Muhammad al-Azdi narrated from Abu Abdullah (as):\n\"My father asked him while I was listening about the extent of illness that permits a person to leave fasting.\nImam (as) said: 'When they are unable to take suhoor (the pre-dawn meal).'\""
        ]
      }
